datasourceFields.name: Time to Close an Incident (seconds)
Max Year?
Time to Close an Incident
datasourceFields.formula:
// This is a calculated field
// It transforms time in seconds into DD:HH:MM:SS format
STR(INT(AVG([Time to Close an Incident (seconds)])/86400)) 
 
+ " day(s) " + 
 
IF (INT(AVG([Time to Close an Incident (seconds)])%86400/3600)) 
< 10 THEN "0" ELSE "" END + STR(INT(AVG([Time to Close an Incident (seconds)])%86400/3600))
 
+ ":" + 
 
IF INT(AVG([Time to Close an Incident (seconds)])%3600/60) 
< 10 THEN "0" ELSE "" END + STR(INT(AVG([Time to Close an Incident (seconds)])%3600/60)) 
 
 
+ ":" + 
 
IF INT(AVG([Time to Close an Incident (seconds)]) %3600 %60) 
< 10 THEN "0" ELSE "" END + STR(INT(AVG([Time to Close an Incident (seconds)]) %3600 %60))

Opened Month Tooltip
datasourceFields.formula:
// This is an IF statment using the opened field to allow for different formats
// original used on columns for line charts are formatted in starting letter of month i.e. J for January
// This version formats to full month name for the tooltip 


// The IF statement names the month based on the month number of the datefield
IF DATEPART('month', [Opened]) = 1 THEN 'January'
ELSEIF DATEPART('month', [Opened]) = 2 THEN 'February'
ELSEIF DATEPART('month', [Opened]) = 3 THEN 'March'
ELSEIF DATEPART('month', [Opened]) = 4 THEN 'April'
ELSEIF DATEPART('month', [Opened]) = 5 THEN 'May'
ELSEIF DATEPART('month', [Opened]) = 6 THEN 'June'
ELSEIF DATEPART('month', [Opened]) = 7 THEN 'July'
ELSEIF DATEPART('month', [Opened]) = 8 THEN 'August'
ELSEIF DATEPART('month', [Opened]) = 9 THEN 'September'
ELSEIF DATEPART('month', [Opened]) = 10 THEN 'October'
ELSEIF DATEPART('month', [Opened]) = 11 THEN 'Novemeber'
ELSEIF DATEPART('month', [Opened]) = 12 THEN 'December'
ELSE NULL
END

datasourceFields.name: Time of Day
datasourceFields.description: Categorises the hours of the day into parts of the day such as "morning". Right click and select edit for more info
datasourceFields.formula:
// This is an IF statement 
// Used to Categorise the 24 hours of a day into parts of the day i.e morning
// scale is 0-23 NOT 1-24


IF DATEPART('hour',[Created At (local time)]) >=1 
    AND DATEPART('hour',[Created At (local time)]) <6 
    THEN "Early AM"

ELSEIF DATEPART('hour',[Created At (local time)]) >=6 
    AND DATEPART('hour',[Created At (local time)]) <12 
    THEN "Morning"

ELSEIF  DATEPART('hour',[Created At (local time)]) >=12 
    AND DATEPART('hour',[Created At (local time)]) <15 
    THEN "Lunch"

ELSEIF DATEPART('hour',[Created At (local time)]) >=15 
    AND DATEPART('hour',[Created At (local time)]) <18 
    THEN "Afternoon"

ELSEIF DATEPART('hour',[Created At (local time)]) >=18 
    AND DATEPART('hour',[Created At (local time)]) <20 
    THEN "Evening"

ELSE "Night"

END

ELSEIF DATEPART('hour',[Created At (local time)]) >=15 
    AND DATEPART('hour',[Created At (local time)]) <18 
    THEN "Afternoon"

ELSEIF DATEPART('hour',[Created At (local time)]) >=18 
    AND DATEPART('hour',[Created At (local time)]) <20 
    THEN "Evening"

ELSE "Night"

END

datasourceFields.name: Above Median?
datasourceFields.formula:
IF AVG([Median]) > 0
THEN "above median"
ELSEIF AVG([Median]) < 0 
THEN "below median"
ELSE "(at median)"
END

datasourceFields.name: Regional Obesity Rate
datasourceFields.formula: {FIXED [Region]: AVG([Adult Obesity (% of pop)])}

datasourceFields.name: Above or Below?
datasourceFields.formula:
IF ROUND([Regional Obesity Rate],2) = ROUND({FIXED [State],[County]: AVG([Adult Obesity (% of pop)])},2)
 THEN "on par with"
ELSEIF ROUND([Regional Obesity Rate],2) < ROUND({FIXED [State],[County]: AVG([Adult Obesity (% of pop)])},2)
 THEN STR(ROUND(([Difference from Region]*100),2)) + "% above"
ELSE STR(ROUND(([Difference from Region]*100),2)) + "% below"
END

datasourceFields.name: Difference from Region
datasourceFields.formula: ABS(ROUND({FIXED [State],[County]: AVG([Adult Obesity (% of pop)])},2)- ROUND([Regional Obesity Rate],2))
